channel.title: Unusual Brands. Very Cheap! Work GREAT! (Hiphone, Apad, PXP, and more.)
channel.description:
Ok so I recently found out about this site called http://www.chinagrabber.com
They have hundreds of rip offs such as the iphone rip called the hiphone. This thing is amazing! I just ordered it and it works great! It looks 100% like the iphone, except on the back instead of it saying iphone there is hiphone. The best part about it was that it only cost me $42.99 with no shipping charge!
I also ordered a PXP. Its a PSP rip off. Again it looks 100% like a psp, but the back logo has PXP and not PSP. It has 32 gigs of memory so you can download roms and play it on the PXP. 11 megapixel camera, mp3, mp4, and mp5 player and so much more. This one cost me $89.99 and so far I havent had any problems with it.
There Ipad rip offs (apad), black berry (black bemy), and all kinds of stuff. If you guys want some really cool shit for hella cheap I suggest going here: http://www.chinagrabber.com .
Here is a pic of my hiphone (brand new still has plastic film on the screen): [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/myhiphone.jpg[/img]
And here is a pic of my PXP-2000 (psp go rip): [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/mypxp-2000_2.jpg[/img]
[u][i][b]I will be ordering more and posting them on this thread as I do![/b][/i][/u]

item.dc:creator: @VBA-Man VBA-Man
item.description:
@VBA-Man wrote:

[quote=“rip4d, post:8, topic:342415”][quote author=Jamie1200 link=topic=438824.msg3225113#msg3225113 date=1275510195]

I’m fairly sure most people don’t use two seperate cameras.

Most people don’t but I do. I have an under water Camera and a “normal one”
[/quote]I mean for normal pictures like these. There are two seperate cameras being used, and I doubt there is any reason as to why.[/quote]They were taken on different days. One I was at home, the other I was at my brothers house.

1EDIT: And actually these are the latest look-a-likes, These ones got great reviews. I have not had one problem with the Hiphone or PXP 2000. The Hiphone is very responsive, and has very few differences with the actual Iphone. You don’t have to trust this site if you don’t want to, its your choice, I was just making this topic for those who did want to check out some of their stuff.

2EDIT: Also there are just as many good reviews as bad reviews just like with any site. And I googled some of these reviews myself and almost all the ‘bad’ reviews all said later that chinagrabber fixed the problem.
